description:
&lt;p&gt;Central West community mental health team, part of the Manchester division of Greater&lt;br /&gt;Manchester Mental health foundation trust, are looking for an enthusiastic General Adult&lt;br /&gt;psychiatry speciality doctor colleague.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a full time appointment for a specialty doctor to work within a community mental health team to support one of the team consultants. This is an established position is currently being filled by a part time locum .&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It is a permanent position&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will work with Dr Varela and Dr Khan long term acting consultant psychiatrists.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The team comprises of care coordinators (CPNs, Social Workers and OTs), a band 7 psychologist, senior practitioners for nursing and senior practitioner for social work.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There is also a nurse-led clinic run by the senior practitioner.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There is no on call commitment but opportunities to participate in middle grade on call are available&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameDr Rosemary ClarkeEmail addressRosemary.clarke@gmmh.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
